						<summary>

						<p>On a slab lying in Survey No. 414 on the way to Ugaragōḷa.</p>						

						<p>Krishṇadēvarāya, 1529 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1451, Sarvadhāri, Māgha śu. 7, Saturday, corresponding to 1529 A.D., January 16. The Śaka year was current.</p>						

						<p>It refers to Vīra-Narasiṅganāyaka and the <hi rend="italic">Durgādhipati</hi> of Toṟagale. ToṟagalevēṇThe and Guṁmagoḷa are mentioned. The inscription is much damaged and the details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
